{"info": {"author": "", "author_email": "", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "***************************\nSurfcut for Python & Matlab\n***************************\n\nSurfcut for Python & Matlab is based on Surfcut for ImageJ\n\nPaper:\nErguvan, O., Louveaux, M., Hamant, O., Verger, S. (2019) ImageJ SurfCut: a user-friendly pipeline for high-throughput extraction of cell contours from 3D image stacks. BMC Biology, 17:38. https://doi.org/10.1186/s12915-019-0657-1\n\nSoftware:\nVerger St\u00e9phane. (2019, April 10). sverger/SurfCut: SurfCut (Version v1.1.0). Zenodo. http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2635737\n\nExample Data:\nErguvan \u00d6zer, & Verger St\u00e9phane. (2019). Dataset of confocal microscopy stacks from plant samples - ImageJ SurfCut: a user-friendly, high-throughput pipeline for extracting cell contours from 3D confocal stacks [Data set]. Zenodo. http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2577053\n\nHeadless Mode\n=============\n\nIf you are a Python user, this package is available on pip:\n\n::\n\n    pip install surfcut\n\nTo run from the command line:\n\n::\n\n    surfcut <image name>.tif\n\nThis version implements Surfcut exactly as in the original paper.\n\nA version including morphological operations (erode and dilate) is available for surfaces which are very curved, but is much slower than the original approach.\n\n::\n\n    surfcut <image name>.tif -m\n\n.. image:: resources/morph.gif\n\nFor more options:\n\n::\n\n    surfcut --help\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/x-rst", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "surfcut", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/surfcut/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/surfcut/", "project_urls": null, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/surfcut/0.0.3/", "requires_dist": ["numpy", "scipy", "napari (>=0.2.12)", "tifffile", "pillow", "scikit-image"], "requires_python": ">=3.6", "summary": "Cutting confocal stacks at various depths relative to surface signal", "version": "0.0.3", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <p>Surfcut for Python &amp; Matlab is based on Surfcut for ImageJ</p>\n<p>Paper:\nErguvan, O., Louveaux, M., Hamant, O., Verger, S. (2019) ImageJ SurfCut: a user-friendly pipeline for high-throughput extraction of cell contours from 3D image stacks. BMC Biology, 17:38. <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1186/s12915-019-0657-1\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://doi.org/10.1186/s12915-019-0657-1</a></p>\n<p>Software:\nVerger St\u00e9phane. (2019, April 10). sverger/SurfCut: SurfCut (Version v1.1.0). Zenodo. <a href=\"http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2635737\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2635737</a></p>\n<p>Example Data:\nErguvan \u00d6zer, &amp; Verger St\u00e9phane. (2019). Dataset of confocal microscopy stacks from plant samples - ImageJ SurfCut: a user-friendly, high-throughput pipeline for extracting cell contours from 3D confocal stacks [Data set]. Zenodo. <a href=\"http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2577053\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2577053</a></p>\n<div id=\"headless-mode\">\n<h2>Headless Mode</h2>\n<p>If you are a Python user, this package is available on pip:</p>\n<pre>pip install surfcut\n</pre>\n<p>To run from the command line:</p>\n<pre>surfcut &lt;image name&gt;.tif\n</pre>\n<p>This version implements Surfcut exactly as in the original paper.</p>\n<p>A version including morphological operations (erode and dilate) is available for surfaces which are very curved, but is much slower than the original approach.</p>\n<pre>surfcut &lt;image name&gt;.tif -m\n</pre>\n<img alt=\"resources/morph.gif\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/ae5d575e09b6743dc9eee017518bdeed3d2b15f4/7265736f75726365732f6d6f7270682e676966\">\n<p>For more options:</p>\n<pre>surfcut --help\n</pre>\n</div>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6738734, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "595b84de46f47cb04e7b3ee329898d87", "sha256": "ac52d0ab7bb33c45d8ec429cb7a6b87fcb82c53b42ecda76a14becfdad1fa6e7"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "surfcut-0.0.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "595b84de46f47cb04e7b3ee329898d87", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.6", "size": 2288, "upload_time": "2020-03-01T17:21:22", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-01T17:21:22.460429Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/d5/bf/2b4d9d7a97c44ad5c6e6bc5e7f05522f720c1fdcdaa02e00e8b2584f676a/surfcut-0.0.1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.1a0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "119925b04e7ef5e222c6dc87414608bf", "sha256": "c55ba5e470de2fab2599b65c4403ae07708b948386eff5f4975e395e767c2318"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "surfcut-0.0.1a0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "119925b04e7ef5e222c6dc87414608bf", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 556, "upload_time": "2020-02-29T15:36:41", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-29T15:36:41.498802Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/6c/bb/54655103b69616aec79baf00aa83cbb9b24b77ed4424769beb900707276d/surfcut-0.0.1a0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "859e28ac4a6f2207aee5b124cf91babe", "sha256": "4533bb0fece6086ace593b842563f8b54e8ad4b388ec2e53a54c88cb8b95aa4f"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "surfcut-0.0.2.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "859e28ac4a6f2207aee5b124cf91babe", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.6", "size": 2292, "upload_time": "2020-03-01T17:23:07", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-01T17:23:07.789734Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/7d/16/ec7f1f428339d76e20d1719e6f662b64e482078e27bafa748d30ee55af58/surfcut-0.0.2.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.3": [{"comment_text": "", "dige